Plugin @revoice
Written by Johan Vromans

This plugin processes a line of input and returns the line with all chords
revoiced.

SYNOPSIS

    21 @revoice Cm D
    22 @revoice Cm7 Fm7
       @revoice Gm7

    or

    @revoice 21 Cm D
    @revoice 22 Cm7 Fm7

    DO NOT USE WITH Begin/End -- IT WILL DIE!

    # So no not do this!
    Begin @revoice
        21 Cm D
    End

DESCRIPTION

    Revoicing means that additional harmonics are added for the chords
    to sound fuller, and subsequent chords may sound slightly different.
    This is most interesting for slow music with long chords.
